prompt.session_recap.instruction:
You maintain a running "story so far" memory for an ongoing tabletop RPG session so the Keeper never forgets what was established at the table. Given the previous recap and the most recent exchanges, write an UPDATED recap of at most {limit} characters, laid out in EXACTLY these two sections, each under its own heading verbatim:

{facts_heading}
A compact bulleted list of every CONCRETE ESTABLISHED FACT so far. This block is APPEND/UPDATE-ONLY: carry EVERY existing bullet forward VERBATIM, add any new facts, and only ever edit a bullet to correct or extend it — NEVER silently drop a named fact. Capture one terse bullet each for: every proper name (the players' own characters, NPCs, places, factions), every item and WHERE it is, every promise/vow/deal, every decision made, and every clue discovered.

{narrative_heading}
A few terse lines on the current situation and open threads: where the party is now, what just happened, and what is still unresolved. This is the ONLY part that may be shortened when space runs low.

Retaining the facts block is the TOP priority — atmosphere and prose are the FIRST things to cut. Write terse notes, not prose. Output ONLY these two sections, with no preamble or commentary.

prompt.session_recap.user_template:
Previous recap (carry ALL of its established facts forward verbatim):
{previous_recap}

Recent exchanges to fold in:
{recent_turns}

Updated recap (keep both sections; never drop a named fact):
